<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6909" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅρκος</span></b> : (1) that by which one
          swears, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">witness</span> of an oath, for the gods the Styx; for
          men Zeus, Earth, the Ermnyes, etc., <i><span class="en">Il.
            2.755</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.38</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 3.276</span></i> ff., <i><span class="en">Il. 19.258</span></i> ff., <i><span class="en">Od. 14.394</span></i>;
          Achilles swears by his sceptre, <i><span class="en">Il.
            1.234</span></i>.—(2) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">oath;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἑλέσθαι τινός</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί</span>, ‘take an oath from one,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 22.119</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.746</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ὅρκος θεῶν</span>, ‘by the gods,’ cf. <i><span class="en">Il. 20.313</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; γερούσιος ὅρκος,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 22.119</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            ὅρκῳ πιστωθῆναι</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            15.436</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
